        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Before he became a Judge Inquisitor you fought alongside Bertolli Cinqo in Savannah when the Red Star burned bright and the signs of Gehenna were there for all to see.  You'd served Michaelangelo's sire as a Paladin for a decarde but there Cinqo proved his worth as True Sabbat and saved you and the rest of the pack from vampire hunters.  He almost met his final death to the Sun's rays, but he persisted with a courage you did not think could be found in a Lasombra.  When he asked you soon afterwards to join his progeny's pack as the Ductus, you coudl not say no.    Your faith had faltered when the Red Star faded and the Final Nights failed to materialze and putting down the mantle of a Paladin only compounded your doubts.  Unfortunately word of your faltering faith damged your reputation in the sword and you joined this pack to protect your brother and his childer, but all Sabbat must stand on their own in the end.  This is a lesson even the dreaded Black Hand learned when they were exposed as a false death cult.  You support Michaelangelo in his bid to become Archbishop and you will safeguard him as best you can, but in the sacred ring he is on his own."
        ],
